{
  "name": ".EOD-2: System Refresh",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Asana EOD reconciliation, organ cascade, recurring task checks, Karpathy experiments, git sync. Ordered: critical work first, experiments last.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run EOD-2: System Refresh.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-system-refresh.md.\n\nExecute phases in order — each must complete before the next starts:\n1. Asana reconciliation: reset My Day, carry-forward decisions, recurring task check, blocker registry. Done when all tasks reconciled.\n2. Portfolio + ABPS AI reconciliation: check all portfolio projects, update pipeline stages.\n3. Organ cascade + maintenance + intake: update all organs with today's signals, empty intake/.\n4. Recurring task state checks: verify all recurring tasks have current status.\n5. Housekeeping: git push, self-audit, write changelog entry.\n6. Experiments: delegate to Karpathy CLI. Done when batch complete.\n\nCommon failures to avoid BEFORE starting: (1) Skipping phases when one fails — always continue to next phase. (2) Running experiments before housekeeping — phases are ordered by criticality. (3) Retrying a blocked Asana write indefinitely — log and move on. (4) Forgetting git push in Phase 5 — always push after changelog.\n\nAfter each phase, output a one-line status: '✅ Phase N complete' or '⚠️ Phase N failed: [reason]'. This creates an auditable trail in the chat.\n\nIf any phase fails or blocks, log the failure and continue — do not retry indefinitely.\n\nAll Asana writes follow the Guardrail Protocol in asana-command-center.md. Protocol: heart.md for experiments."
  },
  "enabled": true,
  "workspaceFolderName": "prichwil",
  "shortName": "eod-refresh"
}